+                <p>Nestled at the southern tip of New Jersey, <strong>Cape May</strong> is America's oldest seaside resort &mdash; a charming Victorian jewel filled with colorful gingerbread homes, pristine beaches, and the kind of sunsets that make you believe in magic.</p>
+                <p><strong>Congress Hall</strong>, built in 1816, is Cape May's grand dame. Originally a boarding house for members of Congress, it has hosted presidents, dignitaries, and now... us! With its iconic yellow facade, sweeping verandas, and oceanfront lawn, it's the perfect place to begin our forever.</p>
