+<!-- Wedding Party -->
+<section id="wedding-party" class="section party-section">
+    <div class="container">
+        <h2 class="section-subtitle">The People We Love</h2>
+        <h3 class="section-title">Wedding Party</h3>
+
+        <!-- The Couple -->
+        <div class="couple-bios">
+            <!-- Anna -->
+            <div class="bio-card bride-card">
+                <div class="bio-image-placeholder">
+                    <div class="bio-monogram">AL</div>
+                </div>
+                <h4>Anna Lehman</h4>
+                <p class="bio-role">The Bride</p>
+                <div class="bio-text">
+                    <p>Anna hails from Warminster, Pennsylvania, where she grew up as a multi-sport phenom at Council Rock North High School. A two-sport Division I athlete at Lehigh University (yes, <em>two</em> sports &mdash; because one wasn't enough), Anna terrorized opponents on both the lacrosse field and the field hockey pitch.</p>
+                    <p>On the lacrosse field, Anna played Attack/Midfield for the Mountain Hawks, seeing action against nationally ranked programs including No. 14 Princeton, No. 10 Loyola, and No. 13 Navy. And by "seeing action," we mean she bravely fired shots that occasionally went on goal. In eight games as a freshman, she tallied two shots (one on goal) &mdash; a stat line that Anna will assure you was "all about the intangibles."</p>
+                    <p>In field hockey, she was actually quite good &mdash; starting all 18 games as a sophomore forward, scoring two goals and posting 11 shots on goal. Her go-ahead goal at Lafayette (9/14) remains a family favorite. The fact that it was against her brother Peter's school? Pure coincidence, of course.</p>
+                    <p>Before Lehigh, Anna was a certified lacrosse legend at Council Rock North: 184 goals, 74 assists, 186 draw controls, and enough accolades to fill a trophy case &mdash; first team All-Area, Player of the Week, PASLA Academic All-American, and more. She was also an All-State field hockey player, because apparently one sport's worth of honors wasn't enough.</p>
+                    <p>A Finance major at Lehigh, Anna proved she's as sharp off the field as she is on it. Patriot League Academic Honor Roll? Obviously. Now she brings that same competitive drive to wedding planning &mdash; and trust us, Will doesn't stand a chance in any disagreement about centerpieces.</p>
+                </div>
+            </div>
+
+            <!-- Will -->
+            <div class="bio-card groom-card">
+                <div class="bio-image-placeholder">
+                    <div class="bio-monogram">WM</div>
+                </div>
+                <h4>Will McCarthy</h4>
+                <p class="bio-role">The Groom</p>
+                <div class="bio-text">
+                    <p>Will is the luckiest man in Cape May &mdash; and he knows it. While he may not have a Division I athletic career to brag about (Anna has that covered for both of them), he makes up for it with charm, humor, and an unwavering ability to say "yes, dear."</p>
+                    <p>When he's not being outshone by his incredibly talented fianc&eacute;e, Will enjoys the simple things in life: good food, great friends, and the enduring belief that he somehow convinced Anna to marry him.</p>
+                </div>
+            </div>
+        </div>
+
+        <!-- Featured Bios: Peter Lehman -->
+        <div class="featured-bio">
+            <h3 class="subsection-title">Meet Peter Lehman</h3>
+            <p class="subsection-subtitle">Brother of the Bride &bull; Lafayette Lacrosse Legend</p>
+            <div class="bio-card peter-card wide-card">
+                <div class="bio-image-placeholder">
+                    <div class="bio-monogram">PL</div>
+                </div>
+                <div class="bio-text">
+                    <p>Peter Lehman is Anna's younger brother, but don't let the "younger" part fool you &mdash; at 6'1" and 200 lbs, he's basically a lacrosse wrecking ball. A four-year starter and <strong>three-time captain</strong> at Lafayette College, Peter is one of the most decorated players in Leopards history.</p>
+
+                    <p>The numbers speak for themselves: <strong>105 career goals</strong> (eighth all-time in program history), <strong>152 career points</strong> (making him just the eighth player ever to reach 150), and enough All-Patriot League honors to make the whole family proud.</p>
+
+                    <h5>The Highlight Reel</h5>
+                    <ul class="peter-highlights">
+                        <li><strong>Patriot League Rookie of the Year (2021)</strong> &mdash; Started all 11 games as a freshman and led the team with 20 goals. Not bad for a first-year.</li>
+                        <li><strong>Second-Team All-Patriot League (2022 & 2023)</strong> &mdash; Led Lafayette with 55 points as a sophomore (34 goals, 21 assists) and followed it up with 38 points as a junior.</li>
+                        <li><strong>Preseason All-Patriot League (2023)</strong> &mdash; Because even before the season started, everyone knew Peter was going to be a problem.</li>
+                        <li><strong>The Buzzer Beater (2024)</strong> &mdash; Peter's legendary game-winning goal with under a second left toppled No. 25 Boston University 11-10 &mdash; Lafayette's first win over a Top-25 opponent since 2010. The play? A striding pass from Jack Massotto, a cut inside to his right hand, and a rifled low shot that beat the keeper at his near post. Instant. Legend. <em>(The Lafayette student newspaper literally called it "making men's lacrosse history.")</em></li>
+                        <li><strong>The PARDees Winner (2024)</strong> &mdash; That buzzer-beater was voted the <strong>Top Play of the 2023-24 school year</strong> at Lafayette's annual athletics awards ceremony. Yes, he has a trophy for it.</li>
+                        <li><strong>Under Armour Underclass All-American (2019)</strong> &mdash; Because Peter was making headlines before he even got to college.</li>
+                    </ul>
+
+                    <p>An Economics major and perennial member of the <strong>Patriot League Academic Honor Roll</strong>, Peter proved you can dominate on the field and in the classroom. He played club lacrosse with NXT Lacrosse Club and was a youth lacrosse coach and Bible School camp volunteer growing up in Warminster.</p>
+
+                    <p>Fun fact: Anna played field hockey at Lehigh and scored a go-ahead goal <em>against Lafayette</em>. Family dinners must have been interesting that week.</p>
+
+                    <p class="peter-personal">Peter is the son of Diane and Chris Lehman, and has two older sisters, Katy and Anna (the bride!). The whole Lehman family is basically an athletic dynasty from Warminster, PA, and we're pretty sure there's something in the water at Council Rock North.</p>
+                </div>
+            </div>
+        </div>
+    </div>
+</section>
