+<section id="faq" class="section faq-section">
+    <div class="container">
+        <h2 class="section-subtitle">Questions?</h2>
+        <h3 class="section-title">Frequently Asked Questions</h3>
+        <div class="faq-list">
+            <details class="faq-item">
+                <summary>What is the dress code?</summary>
+                <p>Cocktail attire for the ceremony and reception. Think elegant but comfortable &mdash; you'll want to dance! For the welcome dinner on Friday, smart casual is perfect. Sunday brunch? Come as you are.</p>
+            </details>
+            <details class="faq-item">
+                <summary>Can I bring a plus one?</summary>
+                <p>Due to limited space, we can only accommodate those listed on your invitation. If you received a plus one, it will be noted on your invite. Please reach out if you have any questions!</p>
+            </details>
+            <details class="faq-item">
+                <summary>Are children welcome?</summary>
+                <p>While we love your little ones, our wedding will be an adults-only celebration. We hope this gives you a chance to enjoy a fun weekend getaway!</p>
+            </details>
+            <details class="faq-item">
+                <summary>Is there parking at Congress Hall?</summary>
+                <p>Yes! Congress Hall has a parking lot available for guests. Street parking is also available throughout Cape May. The venue is very walkable from most accommodations in town.</p>
+            </details>
+            <details class="faq-item">
+                <summary>What's the weather like in Cape May in September?</summary>
+                <p>September is one of the best months in Cape May! Expect warm days (mid-70s°F), cool evenings, and beautiful sunsets. The ocean is still warm enough for a dip! We recommend bringing a light layer for the evening.</p>
+            </details>
+            <details class="faq-item">
+                <summary>When should I RSVP by?</summary>
+                <p>Please RSVP by August 1, 2026 so we can finalize all of our plans. We can't wait to celebrate with you!</p>
+            </details>
+            <details class="faq-item">
+                <summary>What are some things to do in Cape May?</summary>
+                <p>So many things! Visit the Cape May Lighthouse, take a dolphin-watching cruise, explore the Victorian homes on a trolley tour, shop the Washington Street Mall, visit local wineries and breweries, or simply relax on one of the most beautiful beaches on the East Coast.</p>
+            </details>
+            <details class="faq-item">
+                <summary>Will there be an open bar?</summary>
+                <p>Of course! We wouldn't have it any other way. Cheers!</p>
+            </details>
